					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Early statement of Christian belief</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Paris_-_Bibl._Mazarine_-_ms._0924,_f_150v.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Paris_-_Bibl._Mazarine_-_ms._0924%2C_f_150v.jpg/220px-Paris_-_Bibl._Mazarine_-_ms._0924%2C_f_150v.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="555" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/23/Paris_-_Bibl._Mazarine_-_ms._0924%2C_f_150v.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="290" data-file-height="732" /></a><figcaption>Medieval <i>Credo Apostolorum</i>, dated <abbr title="circa">c.</abbr><span style="white-space:nowrap;">&#8201;1300</span> (<a href="/wiki/Biblioth%C3%A8que_Mazarine" title="Bibliothèque Mazarine">Bibliothèque Mazarine</a> ms. 0924 f. 150v). The sequence of attribution to the apostles is:  1. <a href="/wiki/Saint_Peter" title="Saint Peter">Peter</a>, 2. <a href="/wiki/Andrew_the_Apostle" title="Andrew the Apostle">Andrew</a>, 3. <a href="/wiki/John_the_Apostle" title="John the Apostle">John</a>, 4. <a href="/wiki/James,_son_of_Zebedee" class="mw-redirect" title="James, son of Zebedee">James, son of Zebedee</a>, 5. <a href="/wiki/Thomas_the_Apostle" title="Thomas the Apostle">Thomas</a>,  6. <a href="/wiki/James,_son_of_Alphaeus" title="James, son of Alphaeus">James, son of Alphaeus</a>, 7. <a href="/wiki/Philip_the_Apostle" title="Philip the Apostle">Philip</a>, 8. <a href="/wiki/Bartholomew_the_Apostle" title="Bartholomew the Apostle">Bartholomew</a>, 9. <a href="/wiki/Matthew_the_Apostle" title="Matthew the Apostle">Matthew</a>, 10. <a href="/wiki/Simon_the_Zealot" title="Simon the Zealot">Simon the Zealot</a>, 11. <a href="/wiki/Jude_the_Apostle" title="Jude the Apostle">Jude Thaddaeus</a>,  12. <a href="/wiki/Saint_Matthias" class="mw-redirect" title="Saint Matthias">Matthias</a>.</figcaption></figure>
